    bf:summary [ a bf:Summary ;
            rdfs:label "The Coddling of the American Mind is a feature documentary by Ted Balaker and Courtney Moorehead Balaker that's based on The New York Times bestselling book by Greg Lukianoff and Jonathan Haidt. Beginning in 2012, a mental health mystery appeared out of nowhere. Anxiety, depression, and suicide shot up among young people, and nobody knew why. Then one man's brush with suicide revealed some unexpected clues, and five 20-somethings from around the world began to piece together a solution they hoped would pull themselves out of the darkness."@en ] ;
    bf:title [ a bf:Title ;
            rdfs:label "The coddling of the American mind /" ;
            bflc:nonSortNum "4" ;
            bf:mainTitle "The coddling of the American mind /" ] .

